This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a multi-task convolutional neural network architecture optimized for automotive applications. The paper also discusses methods used to optimize the network architecture, such as using native YUV image directly, optimization of layers & feature maps, and applying quantization. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a neural network architecture and discusses methods used to optimize it. 

The paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes a network for autonomous driving, which is a field of AI. 

The paper may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it proposes a network for use in autonomous driving, which is a field of robotics. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-category as it discusses the efficiency of the proposed network for a dedicated CNN accelerator and focuses on memory bandwidth in the design.
